Hands down the best and only hookah 'lounge' in Vegas.
The great atmosphere and friendly service makes for a relaxing night.
The servers came around regularly to check our hookahs, drinks, and food.
I highly recommend this place to anyone looking to enjoy their night.
The hookahs are great (go avalanche mint!
) and the fries are delicious.
My friends and I shared a bowl for just over an hour and only changed flavors because we wanted something new.
Pros: - Great hookas and flavors - Good prices (show your local ID!!!
) - Delicious food - Great and friendly service  - Chill and relaxing atmosphere  - Comfortable seats (couches and chairs, even the ottomans) - Great people and staff - Great DJ and music no matter the day (the entire lounge singing Journey would agree) - Tons of parking - No alcohol - for me this is a pro, there is no drunk a** spilling drinks or being loud and obnoxious  - Extremely clean - the place and the hookahs - It's just the perfect spot  Cons: - The ottomans are small and awesome but they tend to be easy to trip over so just pay attention to where you are going - Honestly I can't think of any.
